169
00:11:15.630 --> 00:11:20.680
In recent years Chinese audiences have also
shown a reticence to Hollywood movies, choosing

170
00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:22.330
Chinese-produced films instead.

171
00:11:22.330 --> 00:11:27.020
Leading to more and more domestic Chinese
films being produced, leading to fewer theatre

172
00:11:27.020 --> 00:11:32.269
screens being available for Hollywood movies,
leading to even less money being made in China

173
00:11:32.269 --> 00:11:34.230
by American studios.

174
00:11:34.230 --> 00:11:38.140
Suddenly that 20% number isn’t sounding
all that great.

175
00:11:38.140 --> 00:11:42.100
The Chinese Government, via their censorship
bureau, is also making it increasingly difficult

176
00:11:42.100 --> 00:11:44.790
for Hollywood movies to get released in China
at all.

177
00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:49.760
In November of 2016, China passed a law banning
content deemed harmful to the “dignity,

178
00:11:49.760 --> 00:11:55.060
honor, and interests” of the People's Republic
and encouraging the promotion of “socialist

179
00:11:55.060 --> 00:11:58.959
core values," approved by the National People's
Congress Standing Committee.

180
00:11:58.959 --> 00:12:04.660
So basically any movie that portrays China
in anything but the most glowing light will

181
00:12:04.660 --> 00:12:06.339
